# Licensing for Redglitch Game Studio

Redglitch Game Studio is dual-licensed to provide both open-source freedom and commercial protection. 

Depending on your use case, you may use this software under one of the following tracks:

---

## 1. Open Source Track (GNU AGPLv3)

For open-source projects, personal learning, and community contributions, this software is licensed under the **GNU Affero General Public License v3 (AGPL-3.0)**. 

### Key Rules under AGPLv3:
* **Attribution:** You must keep all copyright notices, author credits, and license notices intact in the source code and user interface.
* **Share-Alike (Copyleft):** If you modify this software or build upon it, your modified version **must also be open-sourced under the AGPLv3**.
* **Network / SaaS Clause:** If you host a modified version of this engine on a server (e.g., as a cloud service or website) for others to access, you **must make your source code public** to all users accessing the service.

A copy of the full GNU AGPLv3 license text is included below.

---

## 2. Proprietary & Commercial Track

If you want to use, modify, or redistribute Redglitch Game Studio **without** sharing your source code (e.g., in a closed-source product, commercial distribution, or private enterprise application), you cannot use the AGPLv3 track.

Instead, you must obtain a **Commercial License** or explicit written permission from the copyright owner.

For commercial licensing inquiries or custom terms, please contact:
* **Copyright Owner:** Redglitch Engine Authors

